Very cool place. Pleasantly surprised with what has opened up here. The interior is uniquely imagined, with unique shapes and objects covering every inch of the bar room. The ambiance is brought via a record player and they’ve got a decent selection of music from days past to listen to.  Also, they’re having a legend from podcasts past, Matt Fulchiron, doing standup tonite. The owner said he’s talking to Dean Del Ray also. Awesome. The only complaint is they don’t have Bud Light Orange :(

This old "Nook" has been transformed into something new and wonderful.  I was surprised with all the changes.  Went there to celebrate a friend's birthday last night and had a blast.  They have all these neat drinks that aren't on menus at any other establishments I've been to.  Different is the key.  Relaxed,  cozy,  welcoming,  awesome.  The staff were so accommodating,  offering a larger table for our party once one opened up.  A friend who had been to the new "Nook" ordered the table raw oysters which is almost like a rite of passage at Hughti's.  They shucked them perfectly and served them with cocktail and this other sweeter one which was tasty and sweet to try.  I was certainly impressed with this place and will be returning as well as recommending to all. Although in a college town,  I don't believe they will be needing recommendation.  Great place!

Update: Chatted with who I think is the owner, who was very gracious and receptive to my original review. Table service substantially improved since our last visit, and food/cocktails are still consistently stellar. The fact that they attend to reviews and are quick to address them is impressive. So happy we went back to what's turning into our favorite place for food and drinks in Westfield. I highly recommend it.  Original review: I'll start by saying I really like this place - the drinks are incredible, and in particular, their cheese and charcuterie platter is worth the money. Atmosphere is like a 1920's speakeasy. The only setback is that on each visit, our table service took way too long (and it was not that busy) as most attention is given to bar patrons. Most recently, early on a Saturday night, they didn't have the alcohol needed for two of their cocktails, and it took 30 minutes to get the one I ordered. I really want this place to do well, and I still recommend it, just be prepared to wait if you're seated at a table.
